        "text": "## Pb²⁺–Chloride Stability Constant with Multiple Literature Citations\n\n**Measurement selected:** `vlm_177638`\n\n| Property | Value |\n|---|---|\n| **Equilibrium** | Pb²⁺ + Cl⁻ ⇌ PbCl⁺ |\n| **Beta definition** | beta_def_812 (1:1 complex) |\n| **Constant type** | log K |\n| **Value** | **1.07** |\n| **Temperature** | 25 °C |\n| **Ionic strength** | 0.1 mol/L |\n\nThis single measurement is backed by an extraordinary **32 linked citations** spanning 1930–1994. Here are a few representative ones:\n\n| # | Shortcut | Authors | Year | Journal / Source |\n|---|----------|---------|------|------------------|\n| 1 | 30RD | E. C. Righellato and C. W. Davies | 1930 | *Trans. Faraday Soc.*, **26**, 592 |\n| 2 | 31F | H. Fromherz | 1931 | *Z. Phys. Chem.*, **A153**, 376 |\n| 3 | 42GN | A. B. Garrett, M. V. Noble, and S. Miller | 1942 | *J. Chem. Educ.*, **19**, 485 |\n| 4 | 55Na | G. H. Nancollas | 1955 | *J. Chem. Soc.*, 1458 |\n| 5 | 65HP | G. P. Haight, Jr. and J. R. Peterson | 1965 | *Inorg. Chem.*, **4**, 1073 |\n| 6 | 73BH | A. M. Bond and G. Hefter | 1973 | *J. Electroanal. Chem.*, **42**, 1 |\n| 7 | 81BYM | R. H. Byrne, R. W. Young, and W. L. Miller | 1981 | *J. Soln. Chem.*, **10**, 243 |\n| 8 | 84S | T. M. Seward | 1984 | *Geochim. Cosmochim. Acta*, **48**, 121 |\n| 9 | 90H | G. T. Hefter | 1990 | *Polyhedron*, **9**, 2429 |\n| 10 | 94CIO | X. Chen, R. M. Izatt, and J. L. Oscarson | 1994 | *Chem. Rev.*, **94**, 467 |\n\n*(Full list contains 32 citations — only 10 shown for brevity.)*",
